# outcome tendencies
#
# The outcome variables track the org-level tendencies for a given role with regards to bugs being fixed, not fixed, or pending
# Similar to at the profile-level, aggregation at the org-level is done according to orgazniational-actor role will necessarily be
# biased according to the number of times a given role is taken on by each organization
# Therefore, we focus on the "percent" representation of outcome tendencies relative to number of times role is taken on in a manner
# similar to the previous variables
# The percent variable were calculated as continuous at the org-level in the operationalization code, with standard range constraints of 0 to 1 since they represent a rate

# Following the discussion at the profile-level, we separate the "pending" outcomes for analysis for endogeneity and focus on
